      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Happy to side with the newcomers, headed by ARYAAM (1) who has been to the trials twice recently for Anthony and Sam Freedman and won them both. Looks a ready to run type by Snitzel. The stable will be keen to get some cash in the account straight away. Always respect Peter Snowden's youngsters when they first appear, with REBEL ELEGANCE (5) no exception after her strong trial win over 1050m at Randwick last Thursday. Has all the makings of a handy filly. Recent Hawkesbury trial winner SATONO GLOW (6) is a half to dual Gr 2 placegetter Kitty Flash. From the O'Shea/Charlton barn - keep an eye on the betting. Waller first starter LEONESSA (4) trialled twice in February and finished second on each occasion. Expect her to be fully wound up for this. THE WILDLING (8) showed tremendous pace but punctured badly when resuming recently. Likely to offer a bit more resistance with that run under her belt.",
